  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD model employs a single-phase incompressible Navier-Stokes solver with a power-law hemolysis damage accumulation model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger correlation). Thermal effects arising from viscous dissipation and bearing heat transfer — present in the physical CPB pump during extended perfusion runs — are excluded from the model on the basis that they are judged to be of low impact on bulk hemolysis index. No quantitative sensitivity analysis or fidelity trade study has been performed to bound the error introduced by this thermal exclusion, and no validation experiment tests a thermally loaded operating condition.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/hemolysis-worst-case-tolerance",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cfd-identifies-worst-case-hemolysis",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/morrison/model/cfd-cpb-single-phase-isothermal-v2",
