      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Commercial CFD solver with documented V&V test suite; version-controlled simulation scripts.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 used under institutional software quality plan. Solver release notes document regression test suite. Simulation scripts stored in version-controlled repository with change log. Achieved level 2 exceeds required level 1 for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver verified against at least one canonical benchmark with known analytical solution.",
      "rationale": "Solver verified against lid-driven cavity and Poiseuille flow benchmarks. Order-of-accuracy confirmed at 1.95 for momentum equations. Hemolysis transport scalar equation verified against manufactured solution. Achieved level 2 satisfies MRL 2 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) < 5% for QoI hemolysis index at the design operating point.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed (4.2 M, 9.8 M, 21.4 M cells). Richardson extrapolation yields GCI of 3.1% for NIH at the 5 L/min 3000 RPM design point. Discretization error is adequately controlled."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet flow, rotational speed, fluid properties) match simulation inputs within stated uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Bench test flow rates controlled to ±0.05 L/min; rotational speed to ±10 RPM. Fluid viscosity and density characterised at 21 °C and matched in simulation. All five operating points replicated. Thermal boundary conditions not applied in either experiment or simulation, consistent with the isothermal modelling scope."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted NIH within 15% of measured NIH at all five operating points; velocity field mean absolute error < 10%.",
      "rationale": "NIH predictions within 12% of bench measurements across all five operating points. PIV velocity MAE 7.4%. Acceptance criteria satisfied. All comparisons performed under isothermal conditions; no thermally loaded validation point was included in the test matrix."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI is relative hemolysis index RH; model outputs RH directly from Giersiepen-Wurzinger correlation integrated along streamlines.",
      "rationale": "RH is the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 vs predicate). Model integrates scalar hemolysis damage along pathlines and reports RH at pump outlet. QoI is directly comparable to bench NIH measurements. Relevance is high for isothermal conditions tested."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry, fluid, and operating range match COU pump geometry and CPB flow-speed envelope.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the identical FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry at the five COU operating points using porcine blood and blood-analogue fluid. Flow rates (3–6 L/min) and speeds (2500–3500 RPM) span the CPB envelope. Validation activities are judged relevant to the COU. Note: clinical CPB runs at normothermic (37 °C) or hypothermic conditions; all validation experiments were conducted at 21 °C isothermal. The model excludes viscous-dissipation heating and bearing thermal effects, which are present in clinical operation. This exclusion is asserted to be of low impact on bulk hemolysis but has not been quantified and is not tested by any validation activity."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residuals converge to at least 1e-5 for all equations; mass imbalance < 0.01%.",
      "rationale": "Steady-state simulations converged to residuals below 1e-6 for continuity and momentum. Mass imbalance 0.003%. Transient hemolysis scalar converged within 200 iterations per time step. Solver error is negligible."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst; boundary condition assignments documented.",
      "rationale": "Independent peer review of simulation setup files performed by second analyst. Boundary condition assignments, turbulence model selection (SST k-omega), and hemolysis model constants documented in simulation report rev B. No use errors identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Governing equations appropriate for blood pump hemolysis prediction; turbulence model selection justified.",
      "rationale": "Single-phase incompressible Reynolds-averaged Navier-Stokes equations with SST k-omega turbulence closure adopted. Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model applied. Model form is consistent with published FDA pump CFD studies. Thermal energy equation is omitted; viscous dissipation heating and bearing heat transfer to blood are not modelled. The assessment team notes this as a deliberate simplification, arguing the temperature rise over a typical CPB pass is modest and unlikely to alter bulk hemolysis index materially. No fidelity trade study or parametric thermal sensitivity analysis has been conducted to support this assertion, and no validation experiment was designed to probe thermally induced hemolysis enhancement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Blood viscosity, density, and hemolysis model constants characterised and uncertainty documented.",
      "rationale": "Porcine blood rheology characterised at 21 °C (viscosity 3.2 mPa·s, density 1055 kg/m³). Giersiepen-Wurzinger constants C=3.62e-7, alpha=2.416, beta=0.785 adopted from literature. Uncertainty in constants propagated through one-at-a-time sensitivity runs; NIH sensitivity to constant variation ±15% is ±9%. Temperature-dependent viscosity and its effect on shear stress distribution not characterised, consistent with isothermal model scope."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At least three independent blood sample lots used for NIH bench measurements.",
      "rationale": "NIH measurements performed with porcine blood from three independent collection lots. Inter-lot variability in NIH < 8%. Sample characterisation (haematocrit 35±2%, MFI baseline) documented. Adequate for MRL 2 level 1 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; equivalency of non-dimensional groups between validation and COU documented if assessed.",
      "rationale": "Factor not assessed at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 4 requirements. Reynolds number and flow coefficient at validation operating points match COU envelope by design. Thermal equivalency (e.g., Brinkman number) not evaluated, consistent with the isothermal modelling assumption."
    }
  ],
